PLANTS OF DERELICT MINE SITES
Gold Hill Mining District

Voucher for a study of the vegetation on derelict
heavy metal mine sites in the North Carolina Pied-
mont. Site was a Cu and Au (Zn, Pb, Ag) mine.
See herbarium files (Wickland, D.E.) for data.

Herbarium of the University of North Carolina
NORTH CAROLINA
Rowan County

*Galax aphylla* L.

Along stream below lower clearing on the
Randolph Shaft side of the Gold Hill mine
area; site is west of 2352, 0.3 mi. north
of its intersection with 1221.

D. E. Wickland 773 1 October 1975
